@startuml 23_Arch_Compliance_Strategy
!theme plain
title DRE 3D Framework -- Architecture Compliance & Enforcement Strategy

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 8
  BorderColor #90A4AE
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor #F9A825
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #546E7A
  FontSize 9
}

top to bottom direction

' =============================================================
' ARCHITECTURE AS CODE LAYER
' =============================================================
rectangle "Architecture as Code\n(Single Source of Truth)" as AAC #E3F2FD {
  rectangle "PUML Diagrams\n(22 diagrams)\nVisual architecture\nSource of human truth" as PUML #BBDEFB
  rectangle "architecture_spec.yaml\nMachine-readable spec\nTable names, SQL rules\nCRAG params, DRRI def\nAgent hierarchy\nApproval rules" as SPEC #BBDEFB
  rectangle "ADR Registry\n(Architecture Decision\nRecords)\nWhy decisions were made\nWhen to revisit" as ADR #BBDEFB
}

PUML <-right-> SPEC  : must stay\nin sync
SPEC <-right-> ADR   : changes need\nADR reference

' =============================================================
' 4-LAYER ENFORCEMENT PYRAMID
' =============================================================
rectangle "Layer 1 -- Developer (pre-commit, instant feedback)" as L1 #C8E6C9 {
  rectangle "architecture-compliance hook\nScans changed .py files\nagainst architecture_spec.yaml\nFails commit on ERROR findings" as PC1 #A5D6A7
  rectangle "spec-sync guard hook\nBlocks architecture_spec.yaml\nchange without companion\nPUML diagram update" as PC2 #A5D6A7
  rectangle "flake8 + black + pyupgrade\nCode style & quality\n(existing hooks)" as PC3 #A5D6A7
}

rectangle "Layer 2 -- CI/CD (per pull request)" as L2 #FFF9C4 {
  rectangle "pytest test_architecture_compliance.py\nSpec integrity checks\nException registry validation\nFull source scan\nJUnit XML artifact" as CI1 #FFF176
  rectangle "make arch-compliance\nStandalone compliance target\nRuns before main test suite\nBlocks merge on failure" as CI2 #FFF176
  rectangle "make test\nApplication test suite\n(existing)\nCoverage + SonarQube" as CI3 #FFF176
}

rectangle "Layer 3 -- Continuous (SonarQube)" as L3 #FFE0B2 {
  rectangle "sonar-project.properties\nCode quality gate\nSecurity hotspots\nDuplicate detection\nCoverage threshold" as SQ1 #FFCC80
  rectangle "Custom quality gate\nArch compliance score\n= exceptions / total findings\nTarget: < 5% unregistered" as SQ2 #FFCC80
}

rectangle "Layer 4 -- Governance (periodic review)" as L4 #FCE4EC {
  rectangle "Monthly Tech-Debt Review\nExpired exceptions\nTECHNICAL_DEBT items\nException count trend" as GOV1 #F8BBD0
  rectangle "Quarterly Arch Review\nSpec vs reality audit\nNew PUML updates needed\nADR backlog review" as GOV2 #F8BBD0
  rectangle "Exception Registry\n(arch_compliance/exceptions.yaml)\n4 types: INTENTIONAL_DEVIATION\nTECHNICAL_DEBT\nARCH_UPDATE_NEEDED\nWONT_FIX" as EXC #F8BBD0
}

' =============================================================
' DEVIATION DECISION TREE
' =============================================================
rectangle "Deviation Found" as DEV #EF9A9A

rectangle "Decision Tree" as DT #FAFAFA {
  rectangle "Is it a bug in the code?\n-> Fix code now\n   Remove from exception reg" as DT1 #FFCDD2
  rectangle "Is the architecture wrong?\n-> Update PUML + spec\n   Raise ADR\n   Type: ARCH_UPDATE_NEEDED" as DT2 #FFE0B2
  rectangle "Is it a justified tradeoff?\n-> Log INTENTIONAL_DEVIATION\n   Get Tech Lead sign-off\n   No expiry needed" as DT3 #FFF9C4
  rectangle "Is it tech debt?\n-> Log TECHNICAL_DEBT\n   Add ticket_ref + expires_at\n   Review in monthly sprint" as DT4 #E8F5E9
  rectangle "Is it a governance decision?\n-> Log WONT_FIX\n   Get Architecture Board approval\n   Renew annually" as DT5 #E3F2FD
}

DEV -down-> DT
DT  -down-> DT1
DT  -down-> DT2
DT  -down-> DT3
DT  -down-> DT4
DT  -down-> DT5

' =============================================================
' FLOWS
' =============================================================
AAC    -down-> L1 : spec drives\npre-commit rules
L1     -down-> L2 : commit triggers\nCI pipeline
L2     -down-> L3 : PR merge triggers\nSonarQube scan
L3     -down-> L4 : ongoing monitoring\n+ periodic review
L4     -right-> EXC : exceptions managed\nand audited
EXC  ..up..>  SPEC : approved deviations\nfeed back into spec updates

' =============================================================
' WHAT EACH LAYER CATCHES
' =============================================================
note right of L1
  Pre-commit catches (fast, local):
  - Forbidden SQL keywords in new code
  - Unregistered table references
  - Wrong CRAG threshold values
  - check_type not in catalogue
  - DRRI target changed without ADR
  - Spec changed without PUML update
end note

note right of L2
  CI/CD catches (per PR):
  - All pre-commit checks (belt+braces)
  - Expired exceptions blocking merge
  - Missing ticket_ref on TECHNICAL_DEBT
  - Source diagrams deleted/renamed
  - Spec integrity violations
  - Full source tree scan (not just diff)
end note

note right of L3
  SonarQube catches (continuous):
  - Security hotspots in any new code
  - Code duplication across agent layers
  - Test coverage drops below threshold
  - Complexity exceeding component limits
  - Long-term trend in exception count
end note

note right of L4
  Governance catches (periodic):
  - Tech debt exceptions not fixed in time
  - Architecture drifting from diagrams
  - New capability not backed by spec entry
  - Agent hierarchy violations in production
  - DRRI metric definition drift
end note

legend
  <b>Architecture Compliance -- Core Principle</b>
  -----------------------------------------------
  Architecture as Code: the spec is the law.
  Diagrams are the explanation. Code is the implementation.
  All three must stay in sync.

  <b>The golden rule:</b>
  Never change code to deviate from architecture silently.
  Always choose one of: fix code | update spec+PUML | register exception.

  <b>Compliance is NOT a one-time gate</b>
  It is continuous enforcement at every commit, every PR,
  every merge, and every quarterly review. Exceptions are
  debt, not permissions. They expire and must be renewed.
endlegend

@enduml
